In the resource section of this lecture, I provide a link to a gist.

23
00:01:22.980 --> 00:01:28.170
Rather than going through each option, I'm going to provide you with the entire solution.

24
00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:30.510
Copy the code into your clipboard.

25
00:01:32.730 --> 00:01:37.650
Next, open the footer html file in the parts folder.

26
00:01:39.710 --> 00:01:44.150
Let's replace the current template with a new copy of the templates.

27
00:01:46.350 --> 00:01:51.000
Understandably, you may be curious as to how I've created the templates.

28
00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.070
Your solution may be completely different than mine.

29
00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:59.070
Keep in mind, WordPress provides various ways to tackle the same solution.

30
00:01:59.070 --> 00:02:05.310
If your layout is different than mine, that's fine as long as you are able to achieve the same thing

31
00:02:05.310 --> 00:02:06.070
visually.

32
00:02:06.090 --> 00:02:07.150
You're good to go.

33
00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:10.380
Let's walk through my solution in the browser.

34
00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:12.570
Open the footer template file.

35
00:02:14.270 --> 00:02:18.630
You may need to reset the template to view the original templates.

36
00:02:18.650 --> 00:02:22.280
The HTML block should not be inside your template.

37
00:02:22.310 --> 00:02:26.900
Overall, we have a few dozen blocks for creating the footers design.

38
00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:29.930
Most of these blocks should be familiar to you.

39
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:34.130
Starting from the top, everything is wrapped with a group block.

40
00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:37.150
On this block, we're applying three settings.

41
00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:40.970
The first setting changes the text color of the block.

42
00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:46.550
By changing the text color on the group block, children blocks will inherit the color.

43
00:02:46.580 --> 00:02:50.660
This saves us time by modifying the colors on each block.

44
00:02:50.690 --> 00:02:53.780
Secondly, we're changing the background color.

45
00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:57.690
Lastly, we have padding on the block to add breathing room.

46
00:02:57.710 --> 00:03:00.500
They shouldn't be sitting near the edge of the group.

47
00:03:00.620 --> 00:03:03.170
Up next, we have a columns block.

48
00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:05.400
There's not much to say about this block.

49
00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:07.910
We have a total of three columns.

50
00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:10.800
Each column has a heading and paragraph.

51
00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:17.060
The columns block has the class's container and mix auto to center the content.

52
00:03:17.090 --> 00:03:20.900
These same classes can be found on the other blocks too.

53
00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:24.300
Afterward, we have the separator block.

54
00:03:24.320 --> 00:03:26.180
I'm introducing a new block.

55
00:03:26.210 --> 00:03:30.750
The separator block will add a horizontal line across the container.

56
00:03:30.770 --> 00:03:33.080
There are two settings on the block.

57
00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:36.140
Firstly, we're setting the style to wide.

58
00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:40.550
Otherwise the separator block will not stretch from side to side.

59
00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:43.760
Secondly, we're changing the colour to white.

60
00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:47.570
Let's move on to the last block, which is a row block.

61
00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:51.670
It contains the paragraph and social icons blocks.

62
00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:56.530
The row has the space between option enabled for the justification.

63
00:03:56.540 --> 00:04:01.910
This option will allow the children blocks to sit on the opposite ends of each other.

64
00:04:01.940 --> 00:04:04.790
The social icons block is new to us.

65
00:04:04.820 --> 00:04:11.790
As the name suggests, it's a block that can contain a list of social icons under the hood.

66
00:04:11.810 --> 00:04:16.740
They're links that can redirect the user to a business's social media page.

67
00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:21.640
The settings for the icons are mostly unchanged for the style.

68
00:04:21.649 --> 00:04:25.560
I have decided to go with the logo's only option.

69
00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:29.810
This was to remove the background color of the social icons.

70
00:04:29.810 --> 00:04:35.180
As for the color of the icons, they've been modified to white by default.

71
00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:39.680
The color of the icons will be based on the social media platform.

72
00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:43.190
In my opinion, the icons stood out too much.

73
00:04:43.190 --> 00:04:45.860
Setting them to white will match our footer.

74
00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:49.610
I've enabled the open links in new tabs option.

75
00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:55.480
Lastly, I've modified the block spacing option to 0.5 REM.

76
00:04:55.490 --> 00:04:59.150
This option will add spacing between each icon.

77
00:04:59.180 --> 00:05:02.520
Feel free to add any social media icon.

78
00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:05.040
I've added generic platforms.

79
00:05:05.060 --> 00:05:06.150
We're finished.

80
00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:10.040
If we were to view the front end, the footer should be fully functional.

81
00:05:12.240 --> 00:05:13.100
Perfect.

82
00:05:13.110 --> 00:05:15.500
The index template is finished.

83
